9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 543, L.D. 1313, “An Act to Promote
10 Equity in the Forest Products Industry by Allowing Commercial Wood Haulers to Be
11 Eligible for Certain Sales Tax Exemptions and Refunds”
12 Amend the bill by inserting after section 3 the following:
13 'Sec. 4. 36 MRSA §2013, sub-§1, ¶D is enacted to read:
14 D. "Hauling" means the transportation of forest products from the land where the forest
15 products were harvested to their initial destination involving production or use.'
16 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
17 number to read consecutively.
18 SUMMARY
1199 This amendment adds a definition of "hauling" to more narrowly target the sales tax
2200 exemption to the wood hauling industry.
